     "fermionic quantum computation", "fermionic Gaussian state"}, 
    "specialkeywords" -> {}, "tutorialcollectionlinks" -> {}, "index" -> True,
     "label" -> "Quantum Mob/ Q3 Symbol", "language" -> "en", "paclet" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3", "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "WickGreen[ws] returns the n*n matrix of single-particle Green's \
functions characterizing the Wick state (i.e., fermionic Gaussian pure state \
without pairing correlation), where n is the number of fermion modes in ws. \
WickGreen[ws, {k1, k2, ..., km}] returns the m*m matrix of Green's functions \
among fermion modes {k1, k2, ..., km} with respect to ws. WickGreen[data] or \
WickGreen[data, {k1, k2, ..., km}] shows a dynamic progress indicator while \
calculating Green's functions for an (typically large) array data of Wick \
states.", "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> "WickGreen", 
    "titlemodifier" -> "", "metadescription" -> "", "windowtitle" -> 
